inn1.comm: full and straight to begin with, Paine defends
oops, this one goes down leg and doesn't swing back - it's called a wide
another one swings down leg but this time Paine clips it through square to get off the mark
good ball, swinging away from Haddin, and it goes through to Steve Davies, who has the gloves on instead of Matt Prior

dropped at second slip! Anderson draws a genuine edge from Haddin, Yardy dives across to his left, across in front of Strauss, but grasses the chance. That should have been taken, but it was probably the skipper's catch
left alone outside off
banged in at the hips and Haddin gets off the mark with a single worked to square leg
Plunkett begins with a straight ball and Haddin flicks it through midwicket
good placement from Paine as Plunkett goes a touch too straight again, Paine just clips it into the gap between midwicket and mid-on, not trying to hit it too hard
fullish and wide of off, Haddin jams the bat down to drive square through point
wrong line, well down leg side
better line now as Plunkett goes just outside off and angles it back in a touch, it's left alone
another wide down leg side - both bowlers have battled to get the right line so far today
punched to mid-off and can't find the gap
straighter ball now and it's defended away to the off side
again Anderson picks up a thick edge, this one from Paine flies through where a fourth slip might have been, and it runs away to third man
Haddin loves that shot! He backs away just a fraction and slams it inside out over cover for the first boundary of the match - a touch risky, perhaps, but he's hit that one well enough
fuller and straighter now and Haddin drives, but can't beat mid-off
straight-bat defence from Haddin
a bit of width from Anderson and Haddin cuts hard, but straight to point
another one cut straight to point
defended to the leg side
ooh, another leading edge this time from Paine as he tries to flick to leg and it lobs safely short of the man at cover

ah, now, we have a review that could be for both caught and lbw. Paine was walking down the pitch and tried to flick the ball to leg, it's hit him on the pad and lobbed out to cover, where the catch has been taken. So England want to know if it's either lbw or caught, which Paul Reiffel decides against. The review shows that he was hit in line and it was hitting the stumps, with no edge suggested by Hot Spot. And despite being hit so far down the pitch - he's out lbw!
defends it away safely
straight bat from Ferguson as he pushes it back to Plunkett
clipped away off the pads for a single to fine leg
on the back foot now, Ferguson punches to mid-off
full and straight, no swing this time from Anderson, and Ferguson defends
swinging down leg there and would have been a wide, but it's slammed into Ferguson's pad and run away for a leg bye
solidly defended by Haddin, who is one of the few senior players in this Australian side today
pushed away to the leg side this time
Haddin watchfully defends again - he'd love a big innings going in to the World Cup
pushed away defensively to the off side
good bounce and carry through to Davies as this one beats the bat of Ferguson
good shot from Ferguson as he gets a full and straight one and flicks it confidently through square leg, all the way along the ground for his first boundary
solidly defended to the off side now
banged in at the hips and Ferguson works it to midwicket
clipped away through mid-on and this one finds the gap
straight-bat defence from Ferguson now as he pushes it back to Anderson
banged in a touch shorter now and Ferguson sways out of the way
struck on the pads now as it swings down leg and Ferguson can't get it away
quick single now as Ferguson gets on the back foot and punches it to mid-off
another one swings away down the leg side, and again it's not put away, Haddin can only get pad on this and it dribbles away to the on side
again Ferguson is on the back foot, punching an accurate Anderson delivery to mid-off
he begins with a half-volley that Haddin pushes to cover for a quick single
another half-volley from Finn, whose run-up is ever so McGrath-like, and Ferguson pushes to mid-off
Ferguson frees himself up now and gets a much-needed boundary as he backs off a fraction and forces a cut through point, it runs away to the boundary
defended back down the pitch
and there's another boundary from Ferguson, really good wristy stuff as he flicks one off the leg-stump line through midwicket and it's run all the way along the ground, well timed and placed
fuller and straighter, and Ferguson blocks it
good probing line outside off and Haddin just defends to point

Haddin isn't really middling the ball today, and he's moved across outside leg a touch and tried to force it down the ground, but gets an inside edge into his right leg, in a bit of pain there as it got the unpadded section
banged in shorter now and Haddin leaves it alone
again Haddin gives himself room but then just checks his shot and nudges it behind point

Ferguson is gone! Good ball from Anderson as this one bounces sharply outside off and Ferguson fends, and it's well taken high and to the right of Strauss, the only slip in place. Ferguson probably didn't have to play at that bouncer - it wasn't aimed at the body.
banged in at the body and White nudges to leg
full and straight and Haddin meets it with a good on-drive, but straight to mid-on
this one's more gently driven down to mid-on and that allows Haddin to hurry a single
Finn aiming to hit the top of off stump here and White defends with a dead bat
banged in short of a length now and White defends
again Finn is hitting the corridor just on or a touch outside off - White meets it with a straight bat
fuller and a little straighter, White defends to mid-on
Haddin middles this one! And he's smashed it over mid-off for the first six of the match. What a good stroke, he's cleared the fence and that will give him some confidence
Haddin backs away a little and it's beaten him, through to Davies
short of a length again and Haddin defends
swivels a pull away behind square leg now but this is just a single
White gets himself off the mark now, glancing a bad ball down leg and Finn at fine leg slides across to save the boundary
ah, nasty delivery now that jags back in and bounces sharply, it flies off the hip - and possibly bat - and lobs safely short of the man at short fine leg
Finn is banging it in short of a length here but not getting much bounce - White angles the bat and pushes to gully
this one bounces more, and White defends off the back foot
nudged away towards cover and White can't find a gap
again White nudges to off, no run there
ah, great bouncer as it's well directed and White is in all sorts of bother trying to get away from this - it's whacked the shoulder of the bat, just in front of the helmet
banged in shortish again and White can't get it away
again Haddin backs away, as he is wont to do, and it's a swing and a miss
nudges it away towards point and can't find a run
this time Haddin gets it off the middle, as he tries to thump it over cover, but a man in the deep cuts it off
cracking save by Bell at gully! White lashed this cut into the ground and for all money that looked to have beaten Bell, who hurled himself to his left and just got his hand to it
pushed gently towards mid-on now and White does get a single this time
angling a touch down leg and Haddin can't get it away properly, just getting one wide of Davies
Finn continues to bowl well, and Haddin can only push it jumpily to gully
straighter and angling in a touch, Haddin defends
yet another leading edge, and Haddin is very lucky to get away with this. He's shaped to pull, but then stopped halfway through it and the ball has lobbed off his edge short of point
tucked away off the hips for a single
White defends again and can't get a single

hmmm, a boundary, and pretty well played in the end. White has changed his shot halfway through playing it, shaping to pull and then deciding to guide it uppishly wide of the sole slip and it races away to third-man for a boundary. Second slip could have snaffled that, if there was one.
flicked away through square leg for a single
Haddin again backs away and tries to swipe it through cover, but it bounces over the stumps and through to Davies
oh dear, a top edge now as Haddin goes for the pull, and he's again lucky that this one doesn't carry, it falls short of mid-on
nudged away to the off side

England want a review for an lbw shout that is turned down, but this looked to be angling down leg, if there wasn't an inside edge. Let's see. And yes indeed, that was a big inside edge, so the decision stands. Strange that it was reviewed, as none of the England players really went up for the appeal in a big way
Finn rams one in back of a length, as has been England's way today, and Haddin as usual skips leg side of the ball to defend on his toes to cover
dropped by Davies! Oh, no, apparently it's a legbye. Top delivery, turned Haddin right around, flicked the back thigh pad and Davies put down the non-chance diving to his right
good lengths and lines for Finn, enjoying the trampoline bounce and White as usual has the most horridly stiff wrists and cannot work the ball in defence
another clunked back-foot defence. England like it up at White, who doesn't appear to enjoy it
this is short again and finally White wheels away a stiff-armed pull shot that trickles down to fine leg
Haddin continues his exhibition of self-restraint by drawing his bat inside the line and flagging this through to Davies
Plunkett working up some decent wheels with his horridly clunky action and White manages somehow to squeeze this out to third man, half-guide half-cut shot
oops, shoved down the leg side and Plunkett will have to bowl this again
back onto a fine line, hugging off stump and meeting the patient straight bat of Haddin
a touch too straight from Plunkett and it's worked around the corner
Plunkett not following the short-ball plan to White, instead opting for its spiritual opposite - the yorker - which is slightly undercooked and flicked to the leg side
a good short ball that bounces up around off stump is given a  wide. It's because bowlers aren't allowed to be threatening in ODI cricket
this is turning into a lengthy over but Plunkett hasn't actually bowled that badly and this is pushed to cover for a swift single
good finish to the over, Plunkett bangs it in short of a length and White has to stand up to defend uncomfortably

Finn, who is looking oddly orange today, bangs in a short ball that is dropped into the leg side and Finn hares off after it to field. One of the few people still enthusiastic about this seven-match trudge of a series
shortish again and White is resolute in defence, pushing square of the wicket
slower ball from the orangeman, who is not Celtic, as far as I know, well directed too and Haddin defends
quicker this time and it darts past Haddin's attempted back cut
excellent lines and lengths from Haddin, who seems to wear a permanent smile, or smirk if you're English, defends carefully
left alone outside off stump to finish the over
starts well, full of bounding enthusiasm and potential incompetence, on middle and defended
similar delivery to the last and White turns his heavy wrists over the ball to midwicket
Wright lands another good delivery, following Haddin as he backed away, and it's defended back to the bowler
this is slipped down the leg side, and no amount of bright-eyed apology can stop this being a wide
leg-sided again and it thudded off the pads and trickled into the leg side
fullish and straightish and not much the batsman can do but defend
Haddin as usual backs away and this gives him the room to steer behind point
starts well enough, straight, no sign of turn and it's pushed back to the bowler
very short from Yardy, that earns a hint of turn and Haddin has to wait a long, long time to cut to deep point
White is the sort of man that could stand tall and smash this out of Perth, instead he gets down apologetically on one-knee and misses a ramp-sweep. Awful that

smart work from Finn on the long-on boundary sees the end of Haddin! Poor shot really, he just lifted the ball without much intent towards Finn on the boundary, who back-pedalled to take the catch, felt himself about to go over the rope to through the ball up, stepped over before coming back and completing the catch
more careful defence from White, who has remodelled himself on Boycott
yet again White is on the paddle-sweep, he's so tall and bulky it makes no sense, but there you go. He gets enough to earn a single around the corner
White really does hare in, his run up is hilariously quicker than his bowling, the line is good though and it's pushed to mid-on
more good discipline from Wright and Hussey, another who likes to stand leg-side of the ball, defends to cover
left alone outside off stump
for no good reason Wright imagines he has pace and bangs this in short, he doesn't so it sits up invitingly and Hussey does the necessary, thumping this a long way in front of square for four
dropped by Wright, excellent slower ball and Hussey popped it up back to the bowler, they are never easy etc etc, but it should have been taken
Hussey celebrates his let-off in typically measured Hussey fashion, working a single behind square  on the off side
flight! Flight form Yardy! It's nudged around the corner
this is less flighted but the line is good and White's stiff arms can't work a single
full toss is carefully pushed down the ground
wonderful fielding from Plunkett on the square leg boundary saves the four, it was firmly pulled from Hussey and deserved four
short again and it's pulled with less power for a single
pushed into the off side carefully for a single
adverts interrupted this delivery, so I'm not entirely sure what happened. Send your complaints to the BCCI, who should prevent this from happening
ooh, Wright lands this slightly short and the batsman lifted it back towards the bowler who stuck out a hand speculatively but it past him
fuller and straighter and it's carefully defended
the line drifts a touch to leg and it's worked off the pads for one
again this is shortish and at the body, nudged into the leg side
this time White picks it off into the leg side for another single
the over finishes with Hussey pushing to cover
touch short form Yardy but the late cut finds the fielder
White edges down the wicket and works down the ground
again it's pushed down the ground for another single
the sound of time passing slowly - Yardy pushed gently down to long-on
bang! Good grief, to paraphrase Mark Nicholas. Yardy was a touch short and this Hussey got deep into his crease and mowed this into the stands over deep midwicket
defended to finish the over
Wright finds an off-stump line and it's defended
short again, the last occasion White timed the ball was a year ago I think, so his attempted pull is spooned over midwicket
White sits on the back foot and full-faces back to the bowler
touch too leg-sided allows White to turns his hands over the ball
direct hit would have had Hussey out! It was played out to Bell who dived at cover to field smartly, Hussey was still half-way down trying to turn but Bell's throw was well wide
no alarm here, just nudged around the corner
Yardy darts this into the pads and it's flicked away for an easy single
Yardy has another! White tortuous innings ends. White edged down the track but only to bunt this with plenty of inside-edge back to Yardy who gleefully held on to the chance
wow, Yardy finds turn, actual spin past a dangling outside edge
pushed back to the bowler who fields and aims to throw back at the batsman
more careful defence from the front foot
a final forward-block to finish the over
starts with a decent delivery around off stump but Hussey gets leg-side of the ball and opens the face to guide it to third man for four
fuller and firmly pushed back to the bowler
ah top shot again, Hussey gets a touch of width and crashes this backwards of point
yikes, Plunkett has lost his line and length completely and it's cut again firmly but this time to deep cover
better delivery here - full and straight - and defended back to the bowler
hint of extra bounce finds the outside edge and flies off down to third man to finish a good over for Australia
Voges wants to have a dart but Yardy is cramping his for room
Voges down the wicket again and Yardy responded by dropping it shorter, Voges adjusted by cutting very hard to point
this is a touch leg-sided and clips the pads
more of a bat on this and it's driven down the ground
pushed into the on side
excellent flick, fine around the corner earns four, really well played
Plunkett gets his line wrong, shoving this down the leg side
Hussey bunts this gently into the legside and Plunkett runs around to field
short ball and Voges doesn't get much of a pull shot so it trickles away
short and legsided again and once again the pull shot isn't timed all that well
good delivery here, hugging off stump and it's blocked
banged in short, but too short and it sails way over the batsman
Plunkett adjusts his line and finds a fuller length, rewarded with an outside edge that runs down to third man
finishes the over with a full and straight ball that is pushed back to the bowler who fields and throws the ball back at the keeper
Yardy gets his line wrong and is turned around the corner for a single
full and straight and pushed into the off side
pushed wide of cover
Yardy trundles in and is milked down the ground
Hussey gets deep in his crease to steer a full ball past cover
Hussey carefully watches this onto the bat and guides it away for a single
quality start from Trott, he's done this slow-medium very well this tour, and it's carefully defended
wow, good timing here, Trott gets his line wrong and it's flicked through midwicket for four
this is worked to midwicket again but this time just for one
Trott gets his line wrong again, and it's far too full for Davies to get hold of, flicked off the pad down to the fine leg rope
this time the line is better and it's pushed down the ground
full and straight again and pushed down the ground for a jogged single
this skews off an inside edge into the midwicket region
worked again into the leg side but no run
good running earns this guide past over for two
shortish and it's hit to midwicket
careful defence off the front foot
pushed straight to cover for a rapid single to bring up the 150
full and on the legs, turned around the corner
this is shortish and shoved down the leg side
good, bustling back-of-a-length delivery is dropped into the off side for a sharp single
slower ball finds the inside edge of a flowing drive and it runs out to midwicket
another slower ball is driven to mid-off
french-cut gets the boundary! Nips back, flicks an inside edge that runs past the stumps and past the diving Davies
pushed to cover for a quick single to finish the over
Yardy finds a good line but some wonderful timing from a forward-push sees the ball racing to the cover boundary. This partnership has been superb
defended back to the bowler
again it's pushed back at the bowler but a diving Yardy can't cut off the single
touch of inside edge trickles back to the bowler
worked off the pads to midwicket
defended off the front foot, with an inside edge, runs to midwicket to bring up a superb 50
flicked away through square leg
nudged away defensively by Voges
lofted over midwicket now and it's just lobbed short of the man in the deep, a chip shot really

lovely cut shot as Wright gives Voges some width, and Yardy running around from third man stops this with his foot - he's obviously not keen on the dive! Good way to break an ankle, though, if you get it wrong
again too short from Wright, and Hussey pulls to deep midwicket on the bounce
good stuff from Hussey and Voges here, another quick single pushed to cover - and in fact, that has become two, as England get a bit sloppy and allow an overthrow
clipped away to leg and can't find a run
cut down into the ground and it runs away past Davies to third man, but is cut off and they can only manage a single
beautiful cut by Voges! He's waited, cut late and timed it so well that third man can't save it with a sprawling dive to his right, that's a really great stroke
banged in at the hips now and Voges tucks a run through square leg
tickled down towards fine leg now for another run
turned off his pads through square leg again
Wright strays on to the pads too much, and Voges flicks a single down to fine leg
a touch slower from Wright and Hussey can't get it away, a stifled shout as this hits the pads but it was way outside leg
Wright is down leg once more, and Hussey once again tucks a single to fine leg - the scoreboard keeps ticking over
too straight - Wright needs to get across just a tad outside off - and Voges clips another one through square leg
better line this time and Hussey defends to the off side

Hussey goes for the cut now and gets it through point, and that's superb running as they sprint back for two, Hussey narrowly beating a slightly wide throw from Plunkett that is collected by Davies. A better throw and it would have been tight.
Voges clunks a drive into the ground and back to Finn
brilliant late cut! Voges played that same shot in the last over for the same result - this one was even crisper, sailing along the turf and beating third man comfortably.
straighter line from Finn now and Voges nudges to off, thinks of a quick single, and decides against it
Finn goes a little too straight now and Voges tickles a single down to fine leg
defended back down the pitch
wrong line and this is called a wide as Hussey doesn't get anything on an attempted glance
Hussey guides this one wide of the diving gully, shouts "Nooooo!" and then realises it's beaten the fielder, and takes a single
half a shout for lbw as Hussey plays across the line, trying to work it to leg and the ball lobs off his pad to the off side. Wright didn't go through with the appeal, and that was sliding down leg
Hussey meets this with the full face of the bat, trying for a punchy drive past the bowler but Wright hurls himself to his left to save the run
another whippy clip through midwicket, which is a shot Hussey plays a lot. It's not graceful, but it's effective
pushed away to cover and Voges can't get a run
straight ball from Wright and Voges turns it off his hips through square leg
really good, quick running as Hussey nudges to short midwicket and takes off - they picked their fieldsman there, as it was Matt Prior

Plunkett strikes! Hussey tries to turn this one to leg but it's bounced a touch more than he expected and lobbed off the shoulder of the bat towards point, where Bell takes a smart catch diving forward
pushed away to point and Johnson can't find a gap
defended back down the pitch by Johnson
he's off the mark now with a flick to midwicket and Prior's throw misses at the striker's end, where Voges was diving and had made his ground in any case
good sharp running again, Voges pushes forward of point and this throw from Bell does hit the stumps at the non-striker's end but the fast Voges makes it home
well played by Johnson, turns this through midwicket gently to pick up a couple more runs
fullish and straight from Wright, and the drive from Voges finds mid-on
flicked to mid-on and can't find a run
this time Voges does find a gap, flicking it through midwicket
Voges tickles this one behind square leg and there are big cheers from his home crowd at the WACA as he brings up his fifty
defended away safely
punched through cover for a comfortable single
flicked off the hips of Johnson, who will get his eye in for a couple of overs before they think about the Powerplay
Voges defends this with a straight bat
a little too short from Plunkett and Voges is quickly on to this pull, along the ground to deep midwicket for two more
guides this cut to gully and can't beat Bell
good line from Plunkett, giving Voges no width, and it's defended
again Voges gets the late cut away but third man is wider now to cut off those boundaries
a slowish ball to start with and Voges pushes it gently through midwicket

dropped! A tough chance. Well, probably more than tough, but Anderson diving to his left got his hand to this return chance, and he's such a good catcher you'd almost have backed him. It was the slower ball and Johnson could only push it back, uppishly
pushed away to the off side now, uppishly, but cover does the fielding
clipped off the pads to fine leg and brilliant fielding from Yardy, who wasn't even in the frame, but somehow reached the ball and stopped it with his left hand
Johnson gets a single through the off side now
Voges pulls a shorter ball over midwicket, it's collected on the bounce in the deep
curving in to Voges, who pushes it back to Yardy
Voges backs off a touch and cuts hard through point
quicker to Johnson, as you'd expect, and he just pulls to short midwicket
turned off the pads through midwicket, so softly that they pick up two to the man in the deep
darted in at the pads of Johnson, who works a single to deep backward square
Voges cuts but can't beat short third man, that's a good over from Yardy
good ball! Beats the bat outside off, as this one bounces sharply and nips away
well now! Three men on the leg-side boundary, and yet Johnson has still found a gap there! He's flicked it off his hips with a sort of fine pull, and there's nobody there at deep backward square
pushed away to cover for a quick single
tip and run now as Voges nudges it to the leg side, and Anderson runs across towards midwicket to do his own fielding
a bit of swing as Anderson goes fullish, and Johnson clips it along the ground through midwicket and it's sharp running to get back for two
on the pads again and Johnson can't get bat on ball, this one runs off his pads to the off side for a leg bye
the angle makes it hard for Johnson to swing to leg, so he punches a single down towards long-off
Voges takes up a stance well outside leg, and then moves inside it - Yardy spears it down leg and Voges draws the wide
driven down to long-on for another single
bad ball, way down leg, though Davies does well to make the take unsighted
Johnson can't hold it in any more, he's lifted Yardy over the leg side and it's one bounce over the rope at wide midwicket
Johnson is rooted to the crease this time, and he punches it through the leg side as Yardy fires it in much faster
Voges backs off and tries to cut, he just can't connect to a ball that misses leg stump
clips it away through square leg
Voges works it along the ground through midwicket and again it's good running to collect two more
fullish and straight, and Voges punches a drive to mid-off

high, high, higgggh chance from Johnson! And Finn has missed it! Johnson has tried to whack Anderson over midwicket a big leading edge flies a long way up and Finn at short third man runs back, swirls around and totally misjudges it, not an easy one at all
driven clunkily back to Anderson

Prior has taken a stunner in the deep! Oh, he can catch it without gloves after all! Johnson swung from the hips, trying to clear the boundary at midwicket, and Prior was about 10 metres inside, then backed back and leapt high to take the catch above his head - terrific catch.
pulled through midwicket for a couple
Hastings walks across towards leg and this one sails down the leg side - wide is called
good bouncer - well-directed, and Hastings can only fend this away for a run
once again Finn is tricked by the wandering of Voges, who backs off, then walks across outside leg and tries to hook a ball that Finn speared down leg. Wide called.
slower ball from Finn, who decides just to bowl straight, and Voges cuts hard for two runs as Bell at point knocks it down without taking it cleanly
Voges backs away a little and punches it back past Finn for a single
a valuable boundary now as Finn goes down leg once more, and Hastings glances it fine enough to beat the man at fine leg, who makes a desperate but unsuccessful slide
slower ball from Finn, and Hastings nudges a single to the leg side
punched down the ground for a single to long-off
clipped high over midwicket now, more like a chip shot as it lands short of the man in the deep
driven uppishly towards long-on now and and lands safely again, they hare back for a couple more
another England wide, slipped down the leg side
a touch leg-sided again and swung to fine leg
Hastings backed away without looking too sure of what he was doing, Anderson banged it in a touch shorter and a thickish top edge looped out to cover
slower bouncer is wheeled away to deep midwicket and then there is sudden alarm as the batsmen come back for two, not sure how they made it but in the end it was clearly home
Voges backs away and Anderson lands another slow bouncer that is swatted in front of midwicket to end, finally, Anderson's bowling in Australia. He's had an incredible tour
Finn starts the final over by shoving it down the leg side for another wide
how long will this over last!? Banged in short and it sails over the batsman, Davies just about gets a hand on it so they run byes as well
slower ball but crucially it's straight, bunted to mid-on and some very swift running turns one into two
slower ball dragged from outside off stump into the leg side but just for a single this time
Krejza misses a slower ball and cries "aarrgh"
another slower ball but this time Krejza got all of it and it's crunched to deep point
big mow from a length ball skews off the inside edge into the midwicket region
the final ball is sliced over the infield down to deep long-off, Voges finishes unbeaten on 80

inn2.comm: whoosh, Tait starts very quickly and it's left alone outside off stump
have that! Tait strikes with a thunderbolt! Strauss hung back to a full ball and was still half-way through his defensive prod when the inswinger pegged back the top of off stump
fired in a touch shorter and Trott shuffles across his stumps to drop to leg
and this is slung too wide of off. Guess that will happen with him every now and then
Trott opens the face and steers this past point for a jogged single
Davies watches his first ball go down the leg side
ooh, Davies has been out of the game for a while and this was a sleepy drive outside off that swung back between bat and pad
touch shorter this time and Davies sways inside the line to flag it through to Haddin
Bollinger starts well enough outside off stump that is left all alone
Trott shuffles across his stumps and a short ball is flicked off the hip to fine leg
this is dug in very short indeed and it leaps past Davies who left alone. No wide given
touch of swing here, from the bowler and from the batsman, who aimed an airy drive and missed it. This was given a wide, which is a touch harsh
this is shorter and moved away off the seam and left alone
Davies gets bat on ball, without much timing, driven to cover

that is a miserable ending to a poor innings. Length ball and Davies was sitting on the back foot, aimed a swish across the line and the top edge sailed up and Haddin did the rest. This might end quickly
Pietersen gets a bouncer first ball that whistles past the nose
very sharp swinging full ball that Pietersen toe-ended square of the wicket
shoved down the leg side this time. Quick though
slower ball this time, Trott happily pats it to midwicket. Full toss in the end perhaps Trott should have done more with it
very good length and line and Trott defends under his eyes
pace and width draws Trott into a flat-footed waft outside off which he misses
it's another wide, slung down the leg side
variation straight delivery, very straight and full and had Trott stuck on the back foot
good delivery here to finish the over, fullish and swinging away. Solidly blocked to mid-off
good lord, another wide. Bollinger bangs this in short of a length and down the leg side
left alone outside off stump this time, but it's close enough to off stump to prevent a wide
fuller and straighter and carefully blocked, the inside edge carries it around the corner for one
Trott without fuss picks up a single dabbing into the midwicket region
ooh, good ball, nipped back from a length as Pietersen lunged forward and crashed into the elbow of the bottom arm
after all that alarm last delivery Pietersen decides to leave this alone outside off

ah, there's the silly shot, Pietersen walks across his stumps and aims a swish to the midwicket boundary. He missed and it crashed into the body. I suppose if he nailed it, it would have been a great shot
Trott clips a full ball straight of midwicket for three
bit of width from Tait and Pietersen threw his arms at it, toe-ended a bit and it went airily through cover
bit more bat on this drive, still not timed perfectly and it goes through point for a couple more
this is yet another wide, banged in short and down the leg side. Pietersen had an almighty thwack but missed
wide, wide, wide, wide. Short and outside off this time. Pietersen ended up hopping on one leg to aim a swish to off but couldn't reach it
close enough for Pietersen this time to smash a widish offside delivery for four through cover
Pietersen is playing like a millionaire. He's having a bash at absolutely everything. Again he's missed it, clever slower ball dribbled through to Haddin
ah, full half-volley on leg stump and Pietersen clips it powerfully wide of mid-on for four
Trott runs outside leg stump and Bollinger follows him, he still manages to squeeze it out over point for a couple
orthodoxy returns with Bollinger finding a decent length and line and is steered to point
Trott charging down the wicket again and Bollinger follows him again and the drive finds cover
dabbed this time to point
Trott shuffles across his stumps and fiddles this to square leg
Bollinger lands it on a tight line and Pietersen's attempted cut comes off a bottom edge close to the stumps
straight ball on a length is worked through midwicket, with the help of a misfield, for a couple
excellent start from Johnson, very straight and Pietersen is uncomfortable with defence
fuller this time and driven without much timing down the ground for a gentle single. Calmer shot from Pietersen
banged in short, short enough to be called a bouncer, but not a wide
ah, fuller and the width Trott needs to stroke past point, with plenty of timing and it runs away for four
Trott aims a cut shot that finds point, they batsmen went for a single and if Paine had hit, Trott, who had to turn back in a hurry would have gone
short and Pietersen climbed into a pull shot, got most of it and it flew out one-bounce to the midwicket rope
this is straighter and fuller and Pietersen defends
shorter this time but Pietersen was advancing and he has to get on his toes to defend
Pietersen again charging down the crease, Bollinger banged it in shorter and it ended up being driven straight back at him, Bollinger collected and missed as he aimed to throw down the stumps
driven again with a flurry of arms and legs and not much timing down to mid-on
Trott stays deep in his crease and works a single to midwicket
very straight ball finds a very straight bat back to the bowler
enough width for Trott to dab to third man
Pietersen stands very still and throws his arms into a drive that dribbles to mid-off
Pietersen is beaten again outside off stump, aiming a wafty drive
this time he does manage to get bat on ball to a length ball outside off stump, driven to mid-off
Trott departs! Length ball outside off stump, Trott aimed another dab but the edge went through to Hussey at slip. The tour is ending swiftly
Pietersen fiddles this off his pads around the corner for a single to bring the new batsman Ian Bell on strike
Bell gets a shorter ball that he pulls gently down to fine leg
fuller ball to Pietersen, who has calmed down a wee bit after a frantic start, and drives to mid-off
just a hint of width and Bell times an elegant cut shot that speeds to the point boundary
this time Bollinger is straighter and Bell defends with the straightest of blades
again Bollinger is very straight and Bell can do nothing but defend
very full, very wide, Pietersen grunted as he tried to reach it with a flat-footed swish
straighter this time and Pietersen stands tall to defend conventionally
left alone! That's the first sensible shot outside off from Pietersen I can remember
oh dear, this is a full ball that Pietersen aims a pull at, through him in a flash
wider and fuller and Pietersen toe-ends a drive to mid-off. This is quite a struggle
that ends a pretty dreadful innings. Another wide ball full outside off and sliced straight to point. Pietersen's tour ends and it feels like half of him was home already
Matt Prior keeps his first ball out by patting to point
starts outside off stump and Bell shoulders arms
on a length and good line, Bell defends
Hastings offers enough room for Bell to dab to third man
Hastings finds a very straight line and Prior defends again
Prior is away, nudging into the leg side for a swift single
Bell lunges forward to a  full and straight ball to defend
Johnson is full and straight, as is Prior's bat
this is very straight but a touch shorter and Prior steers a defence to point
Prior nudges a single to square leg
Bell tries to work this to leg but gets a hint of leading edge and it runs back to the bowler
some rare amusement for the few England fans at the ground as Johnson slings this miles past off
banged in shorter, much shorter, it was down the legside but not given a wide
left alone outside off stump to end the over
Hastings continues to find a very good line and Bell can only defend
outside off stump this time and Bell opens the face to guide it to third man
pushed firmly into the covers for a swift single
carefully pushed into the off side
Bell down the wicket and pulling airily but it heads out one-bounce to deep midwicket
Johnson gets another, Bell's tour ends. Upper cut to a wide ball straight down to third man who held the simplest of catches. England are heading for the early plane
this is pushed out into the covers
another solid and sturdy defence from Prior
Prior is beaten outside off stump, dangling his bat as it angles past the bat
Prior is more solidly behind this one
finally Prior gets one away, standing tall to steer to third man
defended back down the pitch
ah, a bottom edge now runs on to the pad, and he's lucky it didn't then run on to the stumps
banged in short and Prior goes for the hook, Paul Reiffel at square leg ducks with admirable agility, and that's collected out in the deep
clipped off the pads for a single behind square, and Yardy's off the mark
the lack of pace fools Prior here as he tries to punch a cover-drive off the back foot, can only get another bottom edge down to his feet
the slower bouncer now from Hastings, but it's also the wider bouncer - way outside off
Prior goes for the cut, and can't beat point
Yardy is greeted with a Tait bouncer, and does well to fend it to fine leg for a single
beautiful yorker! Quick and straight, but Prior is up to the task and jams it out, nearly falling over himself in doing so, but he survives
fast and straight again, and Prior punches a square drive through point
on the stumps again and Yardy nudges a single to midwicket
soft hands from Prior as he pushes a single to the leg side
Yardy goes for the dab cut now and finds point
fullish from Hastings and wide of off, Prior drives uppishly through cover to Ferguson, who is sweeping the boundary
and again Prior punches a cover drive through the gap, but hits this one too well and can only get a single
beaten outside off as Yardy tries to push at a ball that angles across him
struck on the pads on leg stump and half a shout for lbw from Hastings, but that must certainly have pitched outside leg
Prior won't mind a bouncer from Hastings, who isn't that quick, and he hooks it on the bounce to deep square leg
wrong line, down leg and Asad Rauf calls that a wide
Yardy leans in to an off-drive and can't find a gap at mid-off
another ripping yorker and it's right on line, but again Prior is good enough to keep it out
lovely shot! Just enough width from Tait, and Prior uses the pace to push a drive through the gap at cover, just timing it and placing it to perfection
nudged into the ground and gully does the fielding
Prior does get this one fine enough to beat gully, guiding it off the back foot to third man
Tait goes for the yorker but this one is just outside off, and Yardy doesn't get bat on ball. If Tait gets a yorker on line to Yardy, it could be goodnight.
nope, wide ball as Tait sprays this one down leg
banged in short of a length and Yardy uses the pace to steer this one behind gully for a single
Krejza is around the wicket to Yardy, drifts it in nicely and Yardy nudges it away to leg
Krejza flights it again and Prior goes for the dab sweep back over his left shoulder, fine leg runs around to field
a paddle away through square leg now
Yardy punches a single through cover - not a lot of turn for Krejza, he's getting some drift though
some spin this time, and Prior gets it off the hip to short fine leg
Prior waits on this and plays it late, cutting fine
pushed away to the off side

beaten outside off. Or is it? Hastings appeals enthusiastically, as does the captain White, although Haddin isn't that interested. Prior tried to dab it away and there must have been a noise. Anyway, White wants a review. Hot Spot doesn't seem to have shown anything, and the not-out decision stands.
bouncer a little down leg now and Prior misses his hook - that's called a wide, the indication coming from square-leg for the height of that ball, which was a touch above the head
good cut from Prior, who gets a single through point

oooh, a run-out chance here as Yardy nudges to off and is slow to react to Prior's call - Hussey from gully collects and throws, but Yardy manages to get his body between the ball and the stumps, so it's hit him on the back of the legs. He might have been short had that got through and hit the stumps
an inside edge through the gate now from Prior, who is lucky not to have played on, but instead he picks up a useful boundary
on the back foot now, Prior steers it to third man
Prior goes for the reverse sweep and he gets it right off the middle of the bat, also getting it fine enough to beat third man
tossed up on line and Prior pushes it back to Krejza
plenty of flight again from Krejza, and a little wide of off, Prior drives hard through cover
soft hands from Prior, as he clips it with the spin towards long on
ah, just too short from Krejza as he tried to rip this and get a lot of spin, Yardy punches it forward of cover point
and again Yardy cuts through the off side with the spin
left alone outside off
cramps Yardy for room and he misses his attempted cut
Yardy gets away with one now, as he tries to hook Hastings and gets a top edge down to fine leg, it looks as though it may carry to Johnson, but in the end it falls a few metres short of him
driven back to Hastings
angling on to the pads of Prior, who clips a run through midwicket
full and straight, and Yardy defends safely
ah! That's what happens when you don't get the reverse sweep right. The ball spins too much for Prior, and runs off his forearm up into his helmet
defended back to Krejza
Prior clips this with the spin through square leg
plenty of air from Krejza, and Yardy advances to make it a full toss, in the end just pushing it back to the bowler
too short, and Yardy has no trouble crunching it through cover
again it's too short, Prior muscles a pull through square leg, but he probably could have done better with that and found a gap
Prior drives comfortably through cover for another single
Yardy this time finds the gap at cover, just getting himself another single
bouncer time, and Prior tries to swipe a hook away but can't connect
half-volley from Hastings, and Prior just steers a drive through cover, happy to tick the scoreboard along with ones and twos
fullish and straight, and Yardy closes the face to work this through midwicket and they pick up two to Paine in the deep
left alone outside off

Krejza has his first ODI wicket! And it comes through a terrific catch from Hussey at cover. Krejza really threw it up and it dropped on Prior, who drove uppishly towards cover and Hussey hurled himself to his right to snare it.
a bit too short from Krejza, but Wright can only tickle it down the leg side to fine leg

oh, a run-out chance goes begging! Wright worked it around the corner to leg, the batsmen took off and then both turned back as Paine got across quickly from short midwicket, but in his dive to the ball Paine has fumbled it and doesn't get his throw away
ah, bad ball. Wright latches quickly on to a short one and thumps a pull through square leg for a boundary
and again Krejza drags it down, and again Wright's eyes light up and he pulls hard through square leg for another four
better ball, fuller and outside off, and Wright cuts late
Wright cuts, and it's well fielded at gully
again Wright tries to cut but Tait is just too quick, it's an under edge that dribbles away to slip
lovely shot from Wright as Tait gives him a half-volley, and it's pushed through cover point without much flair but with excellent timing. Good shot.
and Tait responds with a bouncer! Wright wants nothing to do with a well-directed bumper at 145kph, and he ducks it.
again it's a bouncer - and at 151kph mind you! Wright did try to slap a pull away but was never quick enough on that shot, and Haddin did well to make the take
horrid delivery from Tait, a full toss down leg side which would have been wide, but worse for Australia it's actually a front-foot no-ball, which means a free hit
Tait goes for the slower bouncer, and Wright flays at his free hit, lobbing it up over point but not quite timing it
Yardy has time again as Krejza is just a touch too short, and it's cut away safely
tossed up outside off and turning in, but again it's not full enough, and Wright waits to cut it through cover point
nudged away through point again
Wright tucks it away behind square leg, again it was too short
that's a better ball, fuller and drifting in, Yardy plays it from the crease, defending
defended away to the off side now
tossed up invitingly and Wright actually times a drive
driven carefully to cover
touch of air again and pushed to cover
this is very straight and turned into the leg side
some width from Hussey allows Wright to slash backwards of square
flat just outside off, Wright taps it softly to point, takes a quick single
Wright gets deep into his crease to guide a slightly shortish ball wide of cover
short again and cut out to deep point
Krejza has his second wicket, tossed up outside off stump Wright slashed hard but it looped off the outside edge towards Bollinger who dived forward to short third man to take a tough chance
pushed to backwards square
played backwards of square on the off side for a single
Plunkett lunges forward to defend carefully
Johnson returns and fires this into Yard's pads
this is up outside off stump and it's left all alone
full, straight and crashed into Yardy's pads. It looked very straight by the umpire wasn't interested and the Aussies don't fancy a referral
Yardy opts this time to leave alone outside off
this is slung down the leg side and Yardy can't connect with his attempted fiddle
this is down the leg side again, further than the last
this is straight and pushed down to mid-on
full and tucked around the corner for single
Krejza gives this plenty of air, but it's down the leg side and past the keeper and Tait has to give chase
this is straighter and defended
touch quicker and flatter and again careful defence
back cut from outside off speeds to short third man
Yardy pushes to midwicket and sets off for a very tight single
Plunkett gets across his stumps to work this neatly onto the leg side for one
Johnson lands an absolute pearler, reverse-swinging away past a hapless Plunkett outside edge
this is a touch shorter and Plunkett gets precious bat on ball guiding to deep third man
more reverse swing at a yorker length this time and Yardy jabs it away
beaten again outside off. Plunkett prods forward and it speeds past the outside edge
this time Plunkett decides he's better off leaving alone. Johnson is bowling rather well here

more swing, late and bending away late, it's through Plunkett, getting a pad on its way through to Haddin. Given out by caught but Plunkett reviewed straight away and it was heading over, so can't be lbw and missed the bat, so can't be caught. Great delivery though, Johnson is a man transformed when he gets to Western Australia
little bit short here so even with a fraction of spin and back-foot drive through point is easy
fuller here and pushed to mid-on
too short and Plunkett unfurls a strong pull shot that is fielded smartly on the square-leg boundary
nudged around the corner but straight to the fielder
short and down the legside for another wide
this is dabbed out backwards of square on the off side
turned around the corner but no single available
Yardy swishes a drive through cover
for no particular reason Plunkett misses a prod outside off stump
Plunkett down the wicket but only to check-drive to long-off
this is shoved down the leg side and flicks a pad
Yardy gives himself some room to chop down to deep point
defended with firm wrists to cover
Plunkett, like many of us, has had enough and slugs this high over long-on for six
this time he defends carefully
some extra spin defeats the attempted defence and it runs off the pads
attempted sweep shot goes off the top edge and loops safely towards short fine leg
Yardy can't get this away, defending a fullish ball
down the leg side, attempted sweep finds arm so prevents a wide
outside off stump and missed by Plunkett
this is leg-sided and Plunkett works it very firmly to deep square
Yardy aims a dab sweep but not for the first time he misses
this time Yardy stays up and pushes to cover
Plunkett on the dab sweep now, completing it far better than Yardy to collect a single
Yardy down the wicket and Hussey fires it in quicker but Haddin spills the take
good start from Hastings, on a length at off stump and defended to cover
flash and a miss outside off stump. No real reason for Plunkett to have missed it, but he did
very delicate late dab from off stump guides this through first slip. Actually rather well played
slower bouncer comes off the back of the bat and loops down to fine leg
shortish and cut straight to backwards point
Yardy gets away with another false-shot, he tried to flick this into the midwicket stands but it came off a top edge and looped into space
this is flat and Plunkett pushes to cover with soft, soft hands for a single
flat and quick again and Yardy flicks it around the corner
this is defended back to the bowler
firmly driven but straight to cover
Plunkett picks out mid-on with a flick
Plunkett fetches this from outside off and shoves it to deep midwicket for a well-run couple
Yardy backs away and aims to cut over third man but misses
Yardy gives himself room and this time hacks it over the cover ring for four
Yardy is backing away again, Bollinger follows him and Yardy had to change his shot to a leg-side smack, which he timed well but straight to mid-on
Yardy lands another blow! Getting back in his crease to smack over third man for four
Yardy runs outside leg, then comes back and swishes a couple behind square on the leg side
Yardy backing away again and Bollinger followed and Yardy couldn't get this away
bouncer, and Plunkett can't get bat on ball
Plunket has a slash at one outside off and again it beats the bat
there's the breakthrough the Australians wanted, and it comes through a regulation edge behind, as Plunkett drives hard outside off and Haddin pouches a simple catch
Finn is in now, and he backs away as Tait follows him with a short ball
wide of off now and Finn breathes a sigh of relief as he's allowed to leave it alone
bowled. Base of middle stump. If Tait got a yorker on line, you just knew Finn was in trouble, and he was backing away and trying to slash it through the off side, but Tait was far too quick.
Yardy throws the bat at this pull and gets just enough on it to clear the infield

oh well played! Yardy has smashed this straight back at the bowler, and Bollinger did well to get his head out of the way, so hard was that struck. He had no chance to get the hands up for a catch, and Krejza at mid-off only just saves it
this one is misdirected, down leg and Yardy has managed to get a little tickle on that to get a boundary at fine leg, and that's a good half-century from Yardy
and all of a sudden Yardy has pulled Bollinger for six! What a good shot, he's connected well with this and cleared the rope comfortably, and that's Yardy's highest ODI score
slower ball now, and Yardy doesn't pick it, trying to clear the leg side again, and it thumps him in the chest
good ball, full and straight, but Anderson is good enough to keep it out
Yardy backs away and as a result can't reach this full toss that Tait sprays wide of off
punched away to the off side
again Yardy backs away and Tait follows him, he swivels a pull through midwicket
Tait tries for the yorker but it's well wide of off
banged in at the hips, but a touch too leg-sidey and that's a wide
Tait goes for the slower ball now, and it's well wide of off, Anderson can't get bat on ball
this one sizzles through at 148kph, fortunately for Anderson it was just outside off and he could leave it
slower ball to start with and Yardy punches it to long-off, declining a single
the slower bouncer this time - 102kph, that's almost Yardy's own bowling speed! - and he couldn't get any bat on ball
Yardy swipes a slog out to deep midwicket on the bounce
almost a wicket! Anderson gives himself room and slashes on the up to point, and the ball bounces just short of Tim Paine
this time Anderson finds the gap at point, and that's a lovely cut to get himself off the mark with a boundary
there it is! Australia have won this series 6-1 as Hastings bounces Anderson, who tries for a hook but just gets a top edge that flies high in the air and Haddin takes the catch.
